result.execSummary:
The defendant Jessica L Humphrey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property-Special Facts [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: THE DEPARTMENT OF CORRECTIONS SHALL DEDUCT RESTITUTION AND ALL OTHER COURT OBLIGATIONS AT THE RATE OF 25% OF ALL MONIES RECEIVED WHILE INCARCERATED.
If the defendant's probation is revoked, the conditions of extended supervision shall be the same as the conditions of probation.

miscConds.notes:
Pay restitution in the amount of $463.50. Restitution has been paid in full and disbursed to the victim through the Clerk of Courts Office.
------------------------------

Pay court costs.  **NOTE: THE DEFENDANT IS ORDERED TO PAY ALL COURT OBLIGATIONS TO THE CLERK OF COURTS OFFICE.   Payment is due within 30 days.  If the Defendant cannot make the payment, he/she must report to the Clerk of Courts Office to set up a payment plan.  Failure to comply will result in other collection methods including a civil Judgment and/or suspension of your drivers license for two (2) years.  This judgment may be collected by income assignment if you fail to pay fines and costs as ordered.
------------------------------

No contact with the victim without the victim's and Probation Agent's consent.  No alcohol.  No illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia. May not work in any hospital, nursing home, group home, assisted living facility, or similar facility.
------------------------------
Provide biological specimen to state crime lab for DNA analysis, unless previously provided. Pay DNA analysis surcharge.  Counseling as recommended by Probation Agent.

timeConds.notes: The defendant is to complete one-hundred (100) hours of community service work during EACH year of her three (3) year term of probation with NO BUYOUT. **NOTE: Community service work may be reduced to fifty (50) hours per year of probation if the defendant is employed full time.
